names.details: Nehr-i Ceyḥūn: its another name is Nehr-i Belḫ (River of Belkh). According to Ibn Ḥawqal, its main source rises from the border of Bedaḫşān (Badakhshān) and after joining with many tributaries, it flows westward and northward toward the border of Belḫ (Balkh). Later, it passes by Tirmid. (translated by the creator)
